      "message": "Correct; we now have these three things pinned in go.mod, but \"go get\" doesn\u0027t know to use our go.mod unless cwd is inside our repository.  That\u0027s why I changed to check out the our repo first and run this command inside it.  In go module mode, \"go get -u\" will update the pin to the most recent minor release, which is desirable for a roller or when manually updating, but for this case (and for bots), where we just need to retrieve the dependency at the pinned revision, we just want \"go get\".",
